      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "aromatic-amines",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "Nitration takes place in presence of concentrated\nHNO<sub>3</sub> + concentrated H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>.\n<br><br>In strongly acidic nitration medium, the amine is converted into anilinium ion (– NH<sub>3</sub><sup>+</sup> ); substitution is\nthus controlled not by – NH<sub>2</sub> group but by – NH<sub>3</sub><sup>+</sup> group which, because of its positive charge,\ndirects the entering group to the meta-position instead of ortho and para.\n<img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/7kejek2vdnzd6/15117fff-3c91-40a0-8c9e-3146a2c42090/00d0c2a0-0508-11ea-a7bc-b7b08ce8d541/file-7kejek2vdnzd7-320w.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2017 (Offline) Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 239 English Explanation\">",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "ml98p468",
      "questionNumber": 3,
      "questionText": "<p>Given below are two statements :</p>\n<p><b>Statement I :</b> The dipole moment of R-CN is greater than R-NC and R-NC can</p>\n<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 24th January Evening Shift Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 13 English\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1ml9asa50/ec6e3983-40da-4648-b750-8dfbdf864976/2e2e3850-027b-11f1-bf92-8d689bc79bfa/file-6y3zli1ml9asa51.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1ml9asa50/ec6e3983-40da-4648-b750-8dfbdf864976/2e2e3850-027b-11f1-bf92-8d689bc79bfa/file-6y3zli1ml9asa51.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><b>Statement II :</b> R-CN hydrolyses under acidic medium to produce a compound which on treatment with $\\mathrm{SOCl}_2$, followed by the addition of $\\mathrm{NH}_3$ gives another compound $(\\mathrm{x})$. This compound $(\\mathrm{x})$ on treatment with $\\mathrm{NaOCl} / \\mathrm{NaOH}$ gives a product, that on treatment with $\\mathrm{CHCl}_3 / \\mathrm{KOH} / \\Delta$ produces R-NC</p>\n<p>In the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below</p>",
      "options": [
        "<p>Both Statement I and Statement II are false</p>\n",
        "<p>Statement I is false but Statement II is true</p>\n",
        "<p>Statement I is true but Statement II is false</p>\n",
        "<p>Both Statement I and Statement II are true</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "diazonium-salts-and-other-nitrogen-containing-compounds",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>Statement I : False</p>\n<p>$$ \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{NC} \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}^{+}} \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{NH}_2+\\mathrm{HCOOH} $$</p>\n<p>Statement II : True</p>\n<p>$$ \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{CN} \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}^{+}} \\mathrm{RCOOH} \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{SOCl}_2} \\mathrm{RCOCl} $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{NH}_3} \\mathrm{RCONH}_2 \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{NaOCl} / \\mathrm{OH}^{-}} \\mathrm{RNH}_2 $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{CHCl}_3+\\mathrm{KOH}} \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{NC} $$</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
