    {
      "id": "wjoKdxUduzKwPBBGwpDH6",
      "questionNumber": 5,
      "questionText": "The increasing order of nitration of the following compounds is :\n<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l7u8fp3w/4a9c2672-f958-4c5b-8eb3-250d231a69d7/a2a891c0-301b-11ed-ab58-4f43f7f8c851/file-1l7u8fp3x.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l7u8fp3w/4a9c2672-f958-4c5b-8eb3-250d231a69d7/a2a891c0-301b-11ed-ab58-4f43f7f8c851/file-1l7u8fp3x.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2018 (Online) 15th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 234 English\">",
      "options": [
        "(b) &lt; (a) &lt; (c) &lt; (d)",
        "(a) &lt; (b) &lt; (c) &lt; (d)",
        "(b) &lt; (a) &lt; (d) &lt; (c)",
        "(a) &lt; (b) &lt; (d) &lt; (c)"
      ],
      "correctOption": 3,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "diazonium-salts-and-other-nitrogen-containing-compounds",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "Nitration is an electrophilic substitution reaction. So, the group which increase the electron density on benzene ring will increase the electrophilic substitution reaction.\n<br><br>Here $$-$$ OCH<sub>3</sub> group shows + R effect, but $$-$$ CH<sub>3</sub> group shows + I effect. As + R effect is more effective than + I effect so $$-$$ OCH<sub>3</sub> will increase more electron density on benzene ring. \n<br><br>$$-$$ Cl has strong electron withdrawing effect ($$-$$ I). So it decrease electron density on the benzene ring. \n<br><br> In acidic medium, aniline form anilinium ion.\n<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l7u8h5xi/6bc467fc-20e8-401e-a0e6-81dc92e752ca/cb766e60-301b-11ed-ab58-4f43f7f8c851/file-1l7u8h5xj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l7u8h5xi/6bc467fc-20e8-401e-a0e6-81dc92e752ca/cb766e60-301b-11ed-ab58-4f43f7f8c851/file-1l7u8h5xj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2018 (Online) 15th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 234 English Explanation\"><br>This anilinium ion is least reactive as in benzene ring electron density is least.\n<br><br>$$ \\therefore $$&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The increasing order is (a) &lt; (b) &lt; (d) &lt; (c)",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "YgAdeyDA3KJZzCHRk91klrf5wgq",
      "questionNumber": 6,
      "questionText": "In the following reaction the reason why meta-nitro product also formed is :<br><br>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l9fonu6y/f374df8c-79b7-4d5c-8a2e-3348fdae08c3/c4247fa0-4fb3-11ed-88d9-abb495ae8a3e/file-1l9fonu6z.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l9fonu6y/f374df8c-79b7-4d5c-8a2e-3348fdae08c3/c4247fa0-4fb3-11ed-88d9-abb495ae8a3e/file-1l9fonu6z.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 60vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 24th February Morning Shift Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 187 English\">",
      "options": [
        "–NH<sub>2</sub> group is highly meta-directive",
        "–NO<sub>2</sub> substitution always takes place at meta-position",
        "Formation of anilinium ion",
        "low temperature"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "aromatic-amines",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "Aniline on protonation forms anilinium ion, which is\nmeta-directing. So, a considerable amount of meta product is formed\nalongwith o-nitroaniline and p-nitroaniline.\n<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kxhdusb7/b239e76d-d9b8-4577-90d3-5352880c86c2/79af2230-6310-11ec-b36d-0fa4fbfb1e31/file-1kxhdusb8.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kxhdusb7/b239e76d-d9b8-4577-90d3-5352880c86c2/79af2230-6310-11ec-b36d-0fa4fbfb1e31/file-1kxhdusb8.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 24th February Morning Shift Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 187 English Explanation\">\n<br><p>Nitrating mixture is mixture of conc. HNO<sub>3</sub>\nand a conc. H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>.</p>\n<p>When aniline is reacted with nitrating mixture ortho, meta and para\nnitroanilines are obtained.</p>\n<p>Aniline being basic in nature, reacts with acids to form anilinium ion\nwhich is meta directing.</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
